1 (5) "Healthcare service" means an item or service provided to an
2 individual for the purposes of alleviating, curing, healing, or preventing
3 human illness, injury, or physical disability.
4
5 23-79-2902. Step therapy or fail first protocols prohibited.
6 (a) A healthcare insurer shall not require step therapy protocols or
7 fail first protocols of a lesser device or healthcare service for a
8 prescription or order of a healthcare professional for a noninvasive
9 ventilator if:
10 (1) The noninvasive ventilator requires frequent or substantial
11 servicing as classified by the Centers for Medicare & Medicaid Services and
12 determined by a healthcare professional;
13 (2) There is clinical evidence or enrollee history that suggests
14 the alternative treatments required under the step therapy protocol or fail
15 first protocol will:
16 (A) Be less effective for an enrollee; or
17 (B) Cause an adverse reaction to the enrollee; or
18 (3) The noninvasive ventilator is deemed medically necessary by
19 the United States Food and Drug Administration.
20 (b) The Secretary of the Department of Human Services shall require
21 Medicaid managed care organizations to reimburse for a noninvasive ventilator
22 at no less than one hundred percent (100%) of the fee schedule of the
23 Arkansas Medicaid Program for a ventilator.
24
25 23-79-2903. Rules.
26 (a) The Insurance Commissioner may develop and promulgate rules for
27 the implementation and administration of this subchapter.
28 (b) The Secretary of the Department of Human Services may develop and
29 promulgate rules for the implementation and administration of this subchapter
30 that may apply to the Arkansas Medicaid Program or the Arkansas Health and
31 Opportunity for Me Program under the Arkansas Health and Opportunity for Me
32 Act of 2021, § 23-61-1001 et seq.
33 (c) The State Board of Finance may develop and promulgate rules for
34 the administration of this subchapter for the plans providing health benefits
35 to state and public school employees under § 21-5-401 et seq.
